messages.message:
@Victor Zeng
Hi Team,

It seems we have a data breach?

In Nationwide Prod, the usage looks like our internal data usage, but it is show up in the Nationwide Prod environment.

cc: @Serena @Yash Botadra @Alex Sgueglia @Anshu @Deepthi @Jacky Chen
This should be a P1 incident
@Jet was this raised by customer or us?
This was raised by the customer. The customer said they are no longer seeing this issue as of now.
Yeah, we need to get a confirmation from the customer on this. These screenshots are from last night. @Jet Could we please propose a quick call with NW now?
As of now, the client has confirmed that they no longer see this issue.

@Jet Can we have an EPD ticket for this?
@Yash Botadra We should do some postmortem to understand how this happened and what changed that we are not able to replicate it now.

Definitely! I am surprised that this was only short lived.
Can we ask the customers the time range when they saw this? @Victor Zeng can then probably look into what could have happened that could cause this.

*Aegis has created the incident*
Incident Channel: <#C09E5GPB3S6>
Incident: 767 (https://instabase.app.opsgenie.com/incident/detail/25d2f2c1-d469-433d-9cb5-d2d21e4685ee)

Created by @Jet
We don't store any of the user/workspace/app names in Metronome.

can you post your analysis in this channel?
<#C09E5GPB3S6|>
@Victor Zeng let us please centralize the conversation in the incident channel created.
